<HEADLINE>
GLOBAL FORUM ON NEW DEMOCRACIES SET UP IN TAIPEI
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan.  26 (CNA) 01/27/07  00:11:56 (By Maubo Chang)
</P>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian and five former foreign heads of state
signed in Taipei Friday a declaration for the establishment of
the Global Forum on New Democracies.
</P>
<P>
In the declaration President Chen and former South African
President Frederik Willem de Klerk, former South Korean President
Kim Young Sam, former El Salvador President Francisco Flores,
former Polish  President  Lech Walesa and former Mongolian
President Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat said the first meeting of the
forum will be held in Taipei next year.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Foreign Affairs James Huang said afterward that the
forum initiated by Chen will be a regular gathering for the
world's emerging democracies to draw international attention to
the issues facing them and to enhance Taiwan's international
profile.
</P>
